This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and the mathematical representation of semantics. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it explores methods for learning distributed semantic representations using neural models. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as NLP is a subfield of AI. The paper also mentions state-of-the-art models which apply distributed semantic representations to various tasks in NLP, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) depending on the specific tasks being addressed.
